def movie_review(request):
    movie = request.GET.get('movie')
    date = request.GET.get('date')
    return JsonResponse({"status":"success" , "result" :{"movie_name":movie,"release_date":date}},status = 200)

def movie_review(request):
u r defining a view fun in django
.this fun gets called when ever some1 vivts d url mapped to m_r
.req contains everthing d client sends 
.query para  ?movie=RRR&date=2022-03-25
.Headers
.Body
.Method (GET/POST)


2Ô∏è‚É£ movie = request.GET.get('movie')
request.GET ‚Üí holds all query parameters from the URL.
.get('movie') ‚Üí looks for the query parameter named movie.
Here movie = "RRR"
If the user does not send the parameter, movie will be None.

3Ô∏è‚É£ date = request.GET.get('date')
Same thing as above, but now you extract the parameter date.
From the same URL:
date = "2022-03-25"
If not sent, it also becomes None.

4Ô∏è‚É£ return JsonResponse({...}, status=200)
This sends a JSON response back to the client.
status=200 ‚Üí means ‚ÄúOK / Success‚Äù. ?????????????????
